def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Extract index information
    index = data.index
    index_levels = list(index.levels)
    index_codes = list(index.codes)
    index_names = list(index.names)

    # Extract the specified column level numbers
    cloc_numbers = [index._get_level_number(col) for col in clocs]

    # Determine the levels to unstack based on extracted level numbers
    unstack_levels = [index_levels[i] for i in cloc_numbers]
    unstack_codes = [index_codes[i] for i in cloc_numbers]
    unstack_names = [index_names[i] for i in cloc_numbers]

    unstacked = data.unstack(level=clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    # Update columns based on the unstacked levels
    unstacked.columns = pd.MultiIndex.from_product(unstacked.columns.levels, names=unstack_names)

    return unstacked
